# Device-specific calibration data
# Phase 284 (2026-05-12): bundle starter cursor templates so a fresh
# deploy has working NCC out of the box. Without this, NCC silently
# returns null on every iPad home-screen frame (Phase 281) and the
# pipeline drops to ~0% click rate until templates are re-seeded.
# Templates were extracted from Phase 280 frames where the cursor was
# visibly identifiable; they score 0.85-0.90 against current iPadOS
# cursor. Gitignore everything in data/ EXCEPT cursor-templates/.
data/*
!data/cursor-templates/
# SEED backgrounds — 15 real cursor-free iPad app screens captured live (1.3 MB); the
# reproducibility seed for the cascade verifier (docs/data-and-model-storage.md T1). Not
# regenerable without the iPad, so tracked.
!data/bg-real/
# SEED eval-gate frames — held-out ground-truth accept/reject frames (captured live, ~900KB).
!data/seeds/

# Code Assistants
.mcp.json
.claude
CLAUDE.md

# Nix build artifacts
result
result-*

# Compiled tool binaries (source .swift is tracked; the built binary is not)
tools/ocr/ocr
tools/**/*.o

# ML model binaries — regenerable from the committed training/export scripts (like
# data/). Old cursor-v0..v12 are already tracked (pre-existing ~200MB); this stops NEW
# ones from being committed by an accidental `git add -A`.
ml/*.onnx
ml/*.onnx.data
ml/*.pt
# EXCEPT the shipped detector — tiny (196 KB) + the deployable (docs/data-and-model-storage.md
# T2). Committed so the cascade is ready-to-go without retraining.
!ml/crop-heatmap.onnx

